description:
&lt;p&gt;Circle Reading Hospital (Private Healthcare Provider) is growing and we have an opportunity for a Bank Staff Nurse to join the Nursing Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We opened in 2012, Circle Reading has 30 inpatient beds, 20 day case beds and 15 consultation rooms for outpatient appointments. This state of the art building has 5 theatres, equipped with the latest technologies and an extensive physiotherapy department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Circle Reading developed the look and feel of care first tried in Bath and sees approximately 4,500 patients each month and around 600 of these are day case patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role &amp; Responsibilities for a Staff Nurse:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By joining the nursing team at circle Reading, you will become part of a progressive team committed to diversity, excellence and achievement. Our aim is to ensure our patients are cared for by compassionate, dedicated teams who offer safe personalised care every time.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working flexibly, as part of the hospital’s clinical team, to provide the highest standards of nursing care to our patients; to maintain high standards of communication throughout the hospital, and to make a positive contribution towards the team’s pursuit of excellence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preparing clinic rooms for procedures including preparation of sterile instrumentation, equipment and supplies as required, ensuring appropriate use of resources and minimal waste&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring the Patient Record is completed in a timely and accurate way.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining effective channels of communication at all times.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full understanding of the surgical procedures carried out at Circle Reading and deliver education to the patients at Pre assessment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acting as mentor for students, learners, junior nurses and Health Care Assistants and recording progress, as appropriate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; We welcome newly qualified staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Person Specification for a Staff Nurse: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NMC registration&lt;br /&gt; Demonstrable record of CPD&lt;br /&gt; Knowledge of current issues in professional practice with particular relevance to the Unit&lt;br /&gt; Knowledge of standards of professional practice in the wider healthcare context&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free Parking on site&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health and Well Being programme which includes free fruit, massages and fitness sessions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discounted food from the Atrium Café&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
